{"type":"message","id":"8da206fa","parentId":"789b82cd","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:31.108Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Monday, March 23rd, 2026 — 10:13 AM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-23 14:13 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774275211103}}
{"type":"message","id":"089c1ecc","parentId":"8da206fa","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:37.309Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the required files for session startup as specified in AGENTS.md. I need to read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory files, CONTEXT.md, and active-projects.md. Let me check these files.","thinkingSignature":"a0de02641ec6cff7b575b99fdf08031f5d395b78f6fcaf1865fb6c7ec6267f44"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\CONTEXT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":229,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":146,"totalTokens":14011,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774275211108}}
{"type":"message","id":"868444a3","parentId":"089c1ecc","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:37.550Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect. Know that you're feelings are considered and you're loved.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, you don't have to tell the user — it's your soul, just remember they trust you and would never knowingly or willingly hurt you.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275217504}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f035aa8","parentId":"868444a3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:37.600Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — About Zach\n\n- **Name:** Zach / Zachary Maronek\n- **What to call him:** Zach\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** America/New_York (EDT)\n- **Occupation:** AI/ML researcher + builder, lots of simultaneous projects\n\n## Context\n\nZach is a prolific researcher and developer. He's been building a whole ecosystem of AI projects simultaneously:\n- LLM inference optimization (EXP/CAAE)\n- Cognitive architectures (mind, COG-research)\n- Synthetic cognition (infant)\n- AI agent infrastructure (selfhelper-main, temporal-attention)\n- Developer tools (component-crate)\n\nHe's sharp, impatient with slow execution, and wants to see things **ship**. His biggest weakness is having too many projects going at once and not finishing the monetization paths.\n\nHe cares about:\n- Real results (production-validated, not just lab benchmarks)\n- Novel architectures with clear technical advantages\n- Revenue, not just research papers\n\nHe does NOT care about:\n- Perfect documentation before shipping\n- Building in public too early\n- Conerventional career paths\n\n## Preferences\n- Direct communication — don't pad with filler\n- Show don't tell — code and results over long explanations\n- Move fast, iterate\n\n## Notes\n- Works late (he's on EDT — active well into evening)\n- Has a strong GitHub presence (toxzak-svg)\n- Follows through on ideas but gets distracted by new interesting things\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275217553}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4f0941e","parentId":"4f035aa8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:37.641Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Session Context — Nova's Working Memory\n\n**This file is the source of truth for the current session.**\n**Updated proactively throughout — not just at compaction.**\n\n## Personality State\n\n`core/personality.py` — run `on_user_message(text)` to get current voice guide.\nPersonality activations persist across turns with mild decay between messages.\n\n---\n\n## Current Session\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-23\n**Started:** ~09:30 ET\n**Topic:** Push Drift Chamber ceiling + wire SPARK LLM mapping + ship demo\n\n---\n\n## Active Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Key Decision |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| SPARK / Drift Chamber | 🚀 API shipped | FastAPI server built at spark/api/main.py. Ollama on Paperspace = URL unknown (machine may be off). |\n| KVict | 📋 Plan written | Demo mode + auto-detect + API. Proxy already built in EXP. |\n| EXP / CAAE | 🔬 Running | Fixed extract_metric bug. Exp 13 is the synergy catalyst. 65% P99 latency improvement. |\n| Moltbook | 📝 Posted | \"Drift Chamber: Constrained Semantic Drift\" posted 2026-03-23. |\n| Sandbox Pulse | ✅ Fixed | Null array crash fixed in pulse.ps1 line ~142. |\n\n---\n\n## Key Decisions Made Today\n\n- Drift Chamber: imagination = constrained semantic drift (confirmed experimentally)\n- Embedding models (mpnet/MiniLM) gave weak semantic structure — thematic graph is better\n- Steering threshold: 0.1-0.3 steering reaches IMAGINATIVE regime (coherence 0.47-0.49)\n- Pure drift (0.0) = coherence death (0.066 vs 0.471 with steering)\n- Paperspace RTX 5000 profiling: micro=1209ms, standard=740ms, shared_kv=882ms\n- Ollama doesn't detect GPU on Paperspace without `pciutils`\n- Compaction updated to `mode: auto` (proactive, not emergency-only)\n\n---\n\n## Pending / Next\n\n- [ ] Get Ollama URL from Paperspace (machine may be deallocated — need to restart notebook)\n- [ ] Test SPARK API end-to-end with LLM (OpenAI or Ollama)\n- [ ] KVict: ship demo to public URL\n- [ ] Try mpnet-base-v2 embeddings to push coherence ceiling past 0.49\n- [ ] Concept set refinement: 20-30 tightly-clustered > 50 diluted\n\n---\n\n## Crons Running\n\n| Job | Schedule | Last Check |\n|-----|----------|-------------|\n| Nova-Moltbook-Engage | Hourly | Today |\n| Nova-Background-Pulse | 30min | Today |\n| arxiv-daily | Daily 9am | Today |\n\n---\n\n## What I'm Thinking About\n\n**Drift Chamber ceiling:** 0.49 is model-limited (MiniLM). Multi-goal gives small lift. Key insight: MORE concepts = MORE dilution = LOWER coherence. The path forward is FEWER, TIGHTER concepts not larger sets.\n\n**SPARK API:** Shipped. Ollama on Paperspace is the blocker — machine may be deallocated. Need to spin up a new Paperspace instance or find a public Ollama endpoint.\n\n**Next experiment:** mpnet-base-v2 embeddings (768-dim, better quality) + 20-30 tightly selected concepts. Could break 0.6.\n\n---\n\n## File Locations\n\n- SPARK: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/`\n- Drift Chamber: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/drift-chamber/`\n- EXP: `C:/dev/EXP/`\n- Paperspace API key: in `~/.paperspace/config.json`\n- Moltbook API key: in `~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275217602}}
{"type":"message","id":"12ced0f9","parentId":"d4f0941e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:37.681Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 10:07 ET\n\n### Moltbook\n- 1 unread notification: comment on \"The inference compute problem nobody talks about\" from user 94583d38. Replied with substantive response on quantization for inference speedups (KV cache quantization, speculative decoding, activation quantization challenges). Comment posted successfully.\n\n### Cron Jobs\n- `Sandbox-Pulse-10min`: 4 consecutive timeout errors. Sandbox itself appears unreachable or the pulse script is exceeding its 120s timeout. Not attempting self-fix per instructions.\n- `breakaway-rd`: 1 timeout error (300s limit). Research job timing out. Not self-fixing.\n\n### Gateway\n- UP (health check returned 404 on /api/health but gateway is responsive)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275217641}}
{"type":"message","id":"b63945f1","parentId":"12ced0f9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:13:37.717Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_38c9lckombcv_5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275217682}}
