{"type":"message","id":"8341cddf","parentId":"10e77505","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:12.559Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oqvyyw578j7k_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName       [0m[32;1m Mode [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----       [0m [32;1m---- [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n__pycache__ d---- 3/23/2026 9:41:30 AM\r\nroutes      d---- 3/23/2026 9:41:30 AM\r\n__init__.py -a--- 3/23/2026 9:40:33 AM\r\nmain.py     -a--- 3/23/2026 9:40:58 AM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1697,"aggregated":"[32;1mName       [0m[32;1m Mode [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----       [0m [32;1m---- [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n__pycache__ d---- 3/23/2026 9:41:30 AM\r\nroutes      d---- 3/23/2026 9:41:30 AM\r\n__init__.py -a--- 3/23/2026 9:40:33 AM\r\nmain.py     -a--- 3/23/2026 9:40:58 AM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275252529}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a6575d3","parentId":"8341cddf","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:13.256Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oqvyyw578j7k_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mName           [0m[32;1m Mode [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----           [0m [32;1m---- [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n__pycache__     d---- 3/23/2026 10:09:25 AM\r\nmodal_ollama.py -a--- 3/23/2026 10:09:19 AM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1611,"aggregated":"[32;1mName           [0m[32;1m Mode [0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m----           [0m [32;1m---- [0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\n__pycache__     d---- 3/23/2026 10:09:25 AM\r\nmodal_ollama.py -a--- 3/23/2026 10:09:19 AM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275253208}}
{"type":"message","id":"7f6f7c27","parentId":"1a6575d3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:13.301Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_oqvyyw578j7k_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"SPARK Creative Writing API — /v1/spark/generate\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Optional, List\n\nfrom fastapi import APIRouter, HTTPException\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\n\n# Add spark core to path\nSPARK_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent  # .../spark/\nsys.path.insert(0, str(SPARK_DIR))\nsys.path.insert(0, str(SPARK_DIR.parent))\n\nfrom spark.core.llm_mapper import CreativeMapper\nfrom spark.demo import build_thematic_graph, run_drift\n\nrouter = APIRouter()\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Request / Response models\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nclass GenerateRequest(BaseModel):\n    theme: str = \"love in the age of AI\"\n    domain: str = \"all\"\n    mode: str = \"creative\"  # creative | divergent | exploratory\n    steering: float = 0.3\n    n: int = 3\n    steps: int = 30\n    seed_moment: Optional[str] = None\n    constraints: Optional[List[str]] = None\n    ollama_url: Optional[str] = None\n    model: Optional[str] = None\n\n\nclass Variation(BaseModel):\n    id: str\n    text: str\n    concepts: List[str]\n    coherence_score: float\n    entropy: float\n    regime: str\n\n\nclass GenerateResponse(BaseModel):\n    variations: List[Variation]\n    meta: dict\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Helpers\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef _detect_provider(ollama_url: Optional[str] = None) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"Detect best available provider and URL.\"\"\"\n    if ollama_url:\n        return \"ollama\", ollama_url\n    if os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n        return \"openai\", None\n    if os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n        return \"anthropic\", None\n    if ollama_url := os.environ.get(\"OLLAMA_URL\"):\n        return \"ollama\", ollama_url\n    # Fallback: try localhost\n    return \"ollama\", \"http://localhost:11434\"\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Routes\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n@router.post(\"/v1/spark/generate\", response_model=GenerateResponse)\nasync def generate(req: GenerateRequest):\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate creative text via SPARK's drift chamber.\n\n    The drift chamber activates concepts through semantic diffusion\n    guided by steering toward the theme. Activated concepts are then\n    mapped to prose by an LLM.\n    \"\"\"\n    # 1. Build thematic graph\n    try:\n        graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, all_concepts = build_thematic_graph(req.domain)\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Graph build failed: {e}\")\n\n    # 2. Run drift\n    try:\n        graph, history = run_drift(\n            graph=graph,\n            concept_to_cluster=concept_to_cluster,\n            goal_concepts=goal_concepts,\n            steering=req.steering,\n            steps=req.steps,\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Drift run failed: {e}\")\n\n    # 3. Extract top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_nodes = sorted_nodes[:20]\n    concept_activations = {n.id: n.activation for n in top_nodes if n.activation > 0.05}\n\n    # 4. Map to text via LLM\n    provider, provider_url = _detect_provider(req.ollama_url)\n    model = req.model or (\"qwen2.5:7b\" if provider == \"ollama\" else None)\n\n    try:\n        mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=provider, model=model)\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Mapper init failed: {e}\")\n\n    # Patch Ollama URL if using remote\n    if provider == \"ollama\" and provider_url and provider_url != \"http://localhost:11434\":\n        import requests as _req\n        _original_post = _req.post\n        def _patched_post(url, json, timeout, **kwargs):\n            return _original_post(f\"{provider_url}/api/generate\", json=json, timeout=timeout)\n        _req.post = _patched_post\n\n    try:\n        results = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(\n            concept_activations=concept_activations,\n            theme=req.theme,\n            mode=req.mode,\n            n_variations=req.n,\n            seed_moment=req.seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=req.constraints,\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Text generation failed: {e}\")\n    finally:\n        if provider == \"ollama\" and provider_url and provider_url != \"http://localhost:11434\":\n            _req.post = _original_post\n\n    # 5. Build response\n    strong_count = len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))\n    # Import activation_entropy from drift_chamber (used by demo.py)\n    sys.path.insert(0, str(SPARK_DIR.parent / \"drift-chamber\"))\n    from drift_chamber.metrics import activation_entropy\n    entropy = activation_entropy(graph)\n\n    variations = [\n        Variation(\n            id=r[\"id\"],\n            text=r[\"text\"],\n            concepts=r[\"concepts\"],\n            coherence_score=strong_count / max(len(graph.nodes), 1),\n            entropy=entropy,\n            regime=\"IMAGINATIVE\" if strong_count > 5 else \"EXPLORING\",\n        )\n        for r in results\n    ]\n\n    return GenerateResponse(\n        variations=variations,\n        meta={\n            \"domain\": req.domain,\n            \"mode\": req.mode,\n            \"steering\": req.steering,\n            \"steps\": req.steps,\n            \"provider\": provider,\n            \"n_concepts\": len(graph.nodes),\n            \"strong_concepts\": strong_count,\n            \"entropy\": round(entropy, 3),\n            \"regime\": \"IMAGINATIVE\" if strong_count > 5 else \"EXPLORING\",\n        },\n    )\n\n\n@router.get(\"/v1/spark/domains\")\nasync def list_domains():\n    \"\"\"List available domain configs.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"domains\": [\n            {\"id\": \"all\", \"description\": \"All creative concepts\"},\n            {\"id\": \"romance\", \"description\": \"Love, longing, connection, loss\"},\n            {\"id\": \"scifi\", \"description\": \"Technology, cosmos, humanity, creation\"},\n            {\"id\": \"thriller\", \"description\": \"Tension, power, pursuit, secrets\"},\n            {\"id\": \"literary\", \"description\": \"Craft, meaning, form, expression\"},\n            {\"id\": \"horror\", \"description\": \"Death, dread, flesh, threshold\"},\n            {\"id\": \"poetry\", \"description\": \"Sensory, image, rhythm, metaphor\"},\n        ],\n        \"modes\": [\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"],\n    }\n\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275253255}}
{"type":"message","id":"adae0039","parentId":"7f6f7c27","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:18.068Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me look at the modal_ollama.py file to understand the modal setup, and then I need to figure out what \"finish with modal setup\" means. Modal is a serverless GPU platform. Let me check the existing modal setup and then build out a proper SPARK API deployment on Modal.","thinkingSignature":"0b533d734385fbff02dbd8d639442123bf310d5402b777bdd44f350a79c42c14"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_djpilqg7i8od_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/deploy/modal_ollama.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7273,"output":107,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20973,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774275253302}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f23a630","parentId":"adae0039","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:18.150Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_djpilqg7i8od_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama GPU endpoint on Modal\nDeploy: modal deploy spark.deploy.modal_ollama\nEndpoint: https://spark-ollama-qwen-{user}.modal.run\n\"\"\"\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\nollama_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"requests\", \"httpx\", \"fastapi[standard]\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\"})\n)\n\n\n@app.cls(\n    image=ollama_image,\n    gpu=\"A100\",\n    memory=32768,\n    scaledown_window=600,\n    timeout=3600,\n)\nclass OllamaEndpoint:\n    \"\"\"\n    Ollama on A100 GPU. Model auto-pulls on first generate request (~30s cold start).\n    After that, subsequent requests are fast.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @modal.enter()\n    def start_server(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n        )\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] ollama serve started, pid=\", self._process.pid, file=sys.stderr)\n\n    @modal.exit()\n    def stop_server(self):\n        import os, signal, sys\n\n        print(\"[spark-ollama] Shutting down...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        try:\n            os.killpg(os.getpgid(self._process.pid), signal.SIGTERM)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-generate\")\n    def generate(self, body: dict):\n        \"\"\"\n        body: { prompt: str, model?: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\", options?: { temperature?, num_predict? } }\n        \"\"\"\n        import requests\n\n        payload = {\n            \"model\": body.get(\"model\", \"qwen2.5:7b\"),\n            \"prompt\": body.get(\"prompt\", \"\"),\n            \"stream\": False,\n            \"options\": body.get(\"options\", {}),\n        }\n        resp = requests.post(\n            \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=120,\n        )\n        resp.raise_for_status()\n        return {\"response\": resp.json().get(\"response\", \"\"), \"model\": payload[\"model\"]}\n\n    @modal.fastapi_endpoint(label=\"spark-ollama-qwen-health\")\n    def health(self):\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"spark-ollama\", \"model\": \"qwen2.5:7b\"}\n\n\n@app.local_entrypoint()\ndef test():\n    print(\"spark-ollama module loaded OK\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275258111}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0d90bd5","parentId":"0f23a630","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:27.998Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand what's needed. The modal setup has the Ollama endpoint, but it needs:\n\n1. A web UI for SPARK (a simple web interface)\n2. The modal endpoints are defined but we need to integrate the full SPARK pipeline\n\nLet me look at the core llm_mapper to understand what CreativeMapper does, and then build a proper modal web UI.\n\nActually, looking at the context, the request is to:\n1. Finish with modal setup (the modal_ollama.py is started but might need completion)\n2. Open a UI for SPARK\n\nI think what needs to happen is:\n1. The modal_ollama.py has a basic Ollama GPU endpoint\n\n\n2. But the full SPARK API (FastAPI on port 8765) needs to run on Modal with GPU access\n3. A web UI needs to be built\n\nSo the plan is to create a Modal-compatible version of the full SPARK API that runs with GPU support, then build a simple web UI to interact with it. The existing `deploy/modal_ollama.py` just has Ollama itself, not the full SPARK pipeline.\n\nI need to build out a complete Modal app that runs the SPARK API with an embedded Ollama instance for LLM inference, add a web UI with a nice React or HTML/JS frontend, and get it all deployed. Let me start by checking what the CreativeMapper needs and whether the FastAPI app can run on Modal's infrastructure.","thinkingSignature":"ff2503e0ae80348ca2edf24003797b5dc2c70e546cf10c31d76775f180b4c763"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w71f23i0c05t_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/core/llm_mapper.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w71f23i0c05t_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8041,"output":380,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22014,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774275258153}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0b48c44","parentId":"f0d90bd5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:28.117Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_w71f23i0c05t_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nMap concept activations to creative text using LLM.\nThe prompts here are the voice of SPARK — not Hallmark, not writing-workshop.\nReal prose. Unexpected angles. Precision over platitudes.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport json\nimport random\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Optional, Tuple\n\ntry:\n    import openai\n    OPENAI_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    OPENAI_AVAILABLE = False\n\ntry:\n    import anthropic\n    ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    ANTHROPIC_AVAILABLE = False\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CREATIVE TENSIONS — the core of unexpected combinations\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nCREATIVE_TENSIONS = [\n    (\"light\", \"darkness\", 0.95),\n    (\"creation\", \"destruction\", 0.95),\n    (\"love\", \"hate\", 0.90),\n    (\"order\", \"chaos\", 0.90),\n    (\"birth\", \"death\", 0.90),\n    (\"hope\", \"despair\", 0.85),\n    (\"truth\", \"lie\", 0.85),\n    (\"memory\", \"forgetting\", 0.80),\n    (\"homecoming\", \"exile\", 0.80),\n    (\"embrace\", \"push_away\", 0.80),\n    (\"isolation\", \"connection\", 0.75),\n    (\"rise\", \"fall\", 0.75),\n    (\"identity\", \"other\", 0.75),\n    (\"ghost\", \"flesh\", 0.70),\n    (\"sacred\", \"profane\", 0.70),\n    (\"retribution\", \"mercy\", 0.70),\n    (\"transformation\", \"stasis\", 0.65),\n    (\"confession\", \"secret\", 0.65),\n    (\"pursuit\", \"escape\", 0.65),\n    (\"intimacy\", \"distance\", 0.60),\n    (\"warmth\", \"cold\", 0.70),\n    (\"longing\", \"arrival\", 0.65),\n    (\"loyalty\", \"betrayal\", 0.85),\n    (\"grief\", \"joy\", 0.60),\n    (\"trust\", \"doubt\", 0.75),\n    (\"sacrifice\", \"selfishness\", 0.70),\n    (\"innocent\", \"corrupt\", 0.70),\n    (\"visible\", \"hidden\", 0.65),\n    (\"motion\", \"stillness\", 0.55),\n    (\"voice\", \"silence\", 0.75),\n]\n\n\ndef find_tensions_in_concepts(concepts: List[str], tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]] = None) -> List[Tuple[str, str, float]]:\n    \"\"\"Find which creative tensions are present in a concept set.\"\"\"\n    tensions = tensions or CREATIVE_TENSIONS\n    found = []\n    concept_set = set(concepts)\n    for a, b, w in tensions:\n        if a in concept_set and b in concept_set:\n            found.append((a, b, w))\n    return found\n\n\ndef sample_drift_path(activations: Dict[str, float], n_steps: int = 5) -> List[str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Sample a conceptual drift path through activated concepts.\n    This captures the SEQUENCE of ideation, not just the final state.\n    \"\"\"\n    sorted_concepts = sorted(activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    top = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:30] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    if len(top) <= n_steps:\n        return top\n    \n    # Sample to get a spread across activation levels\n    high = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:10] if a > 0.5]\n    mid = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[10:25] if a > 0.3]\n    low = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[25:] if a > 0.1]\n    \n    path = []\n    steps_per_tier = n_steps // 3\n    for concepts in [high, mid, low]:\n        k = min(len(concepts), steps_per_tier + 1)\n        if k > 0 and concepts:\n            path.extend(random.sample(concepts, k))\n    \n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n_steps]\n\n\ndef build_tension_narrative(tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Build a narrative description of the tensions at work.\"\"\"\n    if not tensions:\n        return \"\"\n    parts = []\n    for a, b, w in tensions[:3]:\n        parts.append(f\"the pull between {a} and {b}\")\n    return \"Through the piece, track: \" + \"; \".join(parts) + \".\"\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# VOICE — the SPARK literary voice\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSPARK_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK. Not a writing workshop. Not a Hallmark card.\nReal prose. The kind where something is at stake.\nPrecision of image. Emotion earned through concrete detail, not declared.\nSentences that do real work. Endings that open rather than close.\nWrite toward what you cannot say directly.\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK creative voice:\n- Ground every abstraction in a concrete sensory moment\n- Let the emotional logic be complex, not simple\n- A character can want two contradictory things\n- What's unsaid matters more than what's said\n- End on an image that contains the whole feeling\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK divergent voice:\n- Break expected form. Break expected rhythm.\n- Let the sentence become the thought\n- Association over narration\n- Surprising juxtapositions earn their place\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE = \"\"\"SPARK exploratory voice:\n- Patient attention to the overlooked\n- Small things seen clearly\n- Restraint is a form of precision\n- Let silence do work\"\"\"\n\n\nclass CreativeMapper:\n    \"\"\"\n    Maps concept activation patterns to creative text.\n    Takes the drift chamber's activated concepts and generates\n    prose that's genuinely surprising — not a Hallmark template.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, provider: str = \"openai\", model: str = None):\n        self.provider = provider\n\n        if provider == \"openai\":\n            self.client = openai.OpenAI(api_key=os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"))\n            self.model = model or \"gpt-4o\"\n        elif provider == \"anthropic\":\n            self.client = anthropic.Anthropic(api_key=os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"))\n            self.model = model or \"claude-sonnet-4-20250514\"\n        elif provider == \"ollama\":\n            self.model = model or \"qwen2.5:7b\"\n        else:\n            raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {provider}\")\n\n    def map_concepts_to_text(\n        self,\n        concept_activations: Dict[str, float],\n        theme: str,\n        mode: str = \"creative\",\n        n_variations: int = 3,\n        seed_moment: str = None,\n        user_constraints: List[str] = None,\n    ) -> List[Dict]:\n        \"\"\"\n        Generate creative text from concept activation patterns.\n\n        Args:\n            concept_activations: Dict of concept_name -> activation (0-1)\n            theme: The driving theme/goal\n            mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n            n_variations: How many text variations to generate\n            seed_moment: A specific moment, character detail, or seed text to anchor the piece\n            user_constraints: List of specific things the user wants in the piece\n        \"\"\"\n        sorted_concepts = sorted(concept_activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n        top_concepts = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[:15] if a > 0.05]\n        mid_concepts = [c for c, a in sorted_concepts[15:30] if a > 0.1]\n        \n        # Sample a drift path for structural guidance\n        drift_path = sample_drift_path(concept_activations, n_steps=5)\n        \n        # Find tensions present in the activated concepts\n        tensions = find_tensions_in_concepts(top_concepts)\n        \n        # Build tension narrative\n        tension_narrative = build_tension_narrative(tensions)\n\n        results = []\n        for i in range(n_variations):\n            prompt = self._build_prompt(\n                theme=theme,\n                top_concepts=top_concepts,\n                mid_concepts=mid_concepts,\n                drift_path=drift_path,\n                tensions=tensions,\n                tension_narrative=tension_narrative,\n                mode=mode,\n                seed_moment=seed_moment,\n                user_constraints=user_constraints,\n            )\n            text = self._generate(prompt, mode)\n            results.append({\n                \"id\": f\"spark_{i+1:03d}\",\n                \"text\": text,\n                \"concepts\": top_concepts[:10],\n                \"drift_path\": drift_path,\n                \"tensions\": [(a, b) for a, b, _ in tensions[:3]],\n                \"mode\": mode,\n                \"theme\": theme,\n                \"seed_moment\": seed_moment,\n            })\n\n        return results\n\n    def _build_prompt(\n        self,\n        theme: str,\n        top_concepts: List[str],\n        mid_concepts: List[str],\n        drift_path: List[str],\n        tensions: List[Tuple[str, str, float]],\n        tension_narrative: str,\n        mode: str,\n        seed_moment: str = None,\n        user_constraints: List[str] = None,\n    ) -> str:\n        \"\"\"\n        Build the actual prompt that will generate interesting prose.\n        This is where SPARK's voice lives — anti-Hallmark, anti-template.\n        \"\"\"\n        \n        # Format concept clusters for the prompt\n        primary = \", \".join(top_concepts[:8]) if top_concepts else \"nothing specific\"\n        secondary = \", \".join(mid_concepts[:5]) if mid_concepts else \"nothing secondary\"\n        drift_str = \" → \".join(drift_path) if drift_path else primary\n        \n        constraints_text = \"\"\n        if user_constraints:\n            constraints_text = \"\\n\\nThe user specifically wants these elements: \" + \"; \".join(user_constraints) + \".\"\n        \n        seed_text = \"\"\n        if seed_moment:\n            seed_text = f\"\"\"\n\\n\\nA seed moment to anchor the piece (incorporate this specifically, don't ignore it):\\n\"{seed_moment}\"\\n\\nLet this moment BREATHE. Build the entire piece around it or from it. Don't paste it in like a requirement — let it become the seed of the story.\"\"\"\n\n        if mode == \"creative\":\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE}\n\nWrite a short piece of literary fiction (200-300 words) that feels alive and surprising.\n\nTheme: {theme}\nPrimary conceptual terrain: {primary}\nSecondary terrain: {secondary}\nThe drift path — the sequence of ideation: {drift_str}\n{tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nDo NOT:\n- Start with \"The [time of day], [character] felt [emotion]\"\n- End with a moral or lesson\n- Use the phrase \"in that moment\"\n- Write a love story that ends with the couple together\n- Use the word \"journey\" unironically\n- Introduce a character as \"a [adjective] [noun]\"\n\nDo:\n- Ground abstractions in specific sensory detail\n- Let the ending open rather than close\n- Make the last image carry the emotional weight\n- Earn your emotion through what you show, not what you tell\"\"\".strip()\n\n        elif mode == \"divergent\":\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE}\n\nWrite a brief, strange, unexpected piece (100-200 words).\n\nTheme: {theme}\nConceptual terrain: {primary}\nThe drift: {drift_str}\nTensions at work: {tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nBreak expected form. Let the piece become what it needs to become.\nIt doesn't have to be a complete story. It can be a fragment with weight.\nIt doesn't have to explain itself.\nAn image that contains an entire world is better than a sentence that explains one.\"\"\".strip()\n\n        else:  # exploratory\n            return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE}\n\nWrite a contemplative piece (200-300 words) about: {theme}\n\n{primary}\n{secondary}\nThe drift: {drift_str}\n{tension_narrative}{constraints_text}{seed_text}\n\nPatient attention to what is. Small things, seen clearly.\nRestraint is a form of precision.\nLet silence do the work that noise would ruin.\nWhat's absent from the sentence matters more than what's in it.\nThe piece should feel like looking — not at something extraordinary, but at something ordinary until it becomes visible.\"\"\".strip()\n\n    def _generate(self, prompt: str, mode: str) -> str:\n        system = {\n            \"creative\": SPARK_CREATIVE_VOICE,\n            \"divergent\": SPARK_DIVERGENT_VOICE,\n            \"exploratory\": SPARK_EXPLORATORY_VOICE,\n        }[mode]\n\n        temperature = {\"creative\": 0.8, \"divergent\": 1.1, \"exploratory\": 0.7}[mode]\n        max_tokens = {\"creative\": 600, \"divergent\": 400, \"exploratory\": 600}[mode]\n\n        if self.provider == \"openai\":\n            response = self.client.chat.completions.create(\n                model=self.model,\n                messages=[\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are SPARK. Literary. Precise. Unexpected. Write prose that earns its emotion.\"},\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt},\n                ],\n                temperature=temperature,\n                max_tokens=max_tokens,\n            )\n            return response.choices[0].message.content\n\n        elif self.provider == \"anthropic\":\n            response = self.client.messages.create(\n                model=self.model,\n                max_tokens=max_tokens,\n                system=\"You are SPARK. Literary. Precise. Unexpected. Write prose that earns its emotion.\",\n                messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n                temperature=temperature,\n            )\n            return response.content[0].text\n\n        elif self.provider == \"ollama\":\n            import requests\n            full_prompt = f\"{SPARK_VOICE}\\n\\n{prompt}\"\n            response = requests.post(\n                \"http://localhost:11434/api/generate\",\n                json={\n                    \"model\": self.model,\n                    \"prompt\": full_prompt,\n                    \"stream\": False,\n                    \"options\": {\"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": max_tokens},\n                },\n                timeout=90,\n            )\n            return response.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {self.provider}\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275268074}}
{"type":"message","id":"65f3bf09","parentId":"f0b48c44","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:28.162Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_w71f23i0c05t_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\nDrift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM → Creative Text\n\nUsage:\n    python demo.py                          # Interactive mode\n    python demo.py --domain romance --steering 0.3 --n 2  # Headless\n    python demo.py --ollama-url http://localhost:11434  # Use Ollama\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport argparse\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add project root so 'spark' is importable\nSPARK_DIR = Path(__file__).parent  # .../spark/\nPROJECTS_DIR = SPARK_DIR.parent     # .../projects/\nsys.path.insert(0, str(SPARK_DIR))\nsys.path.insert(0, str(PROJECTS_DIR))\n\nfrom drift_chamber import (\n    ConceptGraph, ConceptNode,\n    DriftChamberConfig,\n    drift_cycle, decay,\n    activation_entropy,\n)\n\nfrom spark.core.thematic_graph import CONCEPT_CLUSTERS, CREATIVE_TENSIONS, WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# THEME GRAPH BUILDER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef build_thematic_graph(domain: str = \"all\") -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Build concept graph from thematic universe.\n    Returns (graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts)\n    \"\"\"\n    # Domain-specific concept selection\n    DOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n        \"all\": {\n            \"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"romance\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"scifi\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"creative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"thriller\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"mortality\", \"narrative\", \"relationships\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"literary\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"literary\", \"narrative\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"literary\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"horror\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\", \"cosmos\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n        \"poetry\": {\n            \"clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\", \"sensory\", \"literary\"],\n            \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"sensory\"],\n            \"extra_weight\": {},\n        },\n    }\n\n    if domain not in DOMAIN_CONFIGS:\n        domain = \"all\"\n\n    config = DOMAIN_CONFIGS[domain]\n\n    # Select concepts\n    selected_concepts = []\n    for cluster_name in config[\"clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if concept not in selected_concepts:\n                    selected_concepts.append(concept)\n\n    # Build concept_to_cluster\n    concept_to_cluster = {}\n    for cluster_name, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n        for c in concepts:\n            if c not in concept_to_cluster:\n                concept_to_cluster[c] = cluster_name\n\n    # Build adjacency — SPARSE: limit per-node degree to prevent equalization\n    # Fully-connected within-cluster = all activations equalize instantly\n    # Fix: connect each node to max K nearest neighbors within cluster\n    MAX_WITHIN_K = 8   # Max within-cluster neighbors per node\n    MAX_CROSS_K = 4    # Max cross-cluster neighbors per node\n    CROSS_WEIGHTS = {\n        (\"emotions\", \"relationships\"): 0.8,\n        (\"emotions\", \"sensory\"): 0.5,\n        (\"narrative\", \"archetypes\"): 0.7,\n        (\"creative\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"creative\", \"sensory\"): 0.4,\n        (\"mortality\", \"emotions\"): 0.6,\n        (\"mortality\", \"cosmos\"): 0.5,\n    }\n\n    # Pre-compute tension pairs for within-cluster edge discovery\n    TENSION_PAIRS = {(a, b) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS} | {(b, a) for a, b, _ in CREATIVE_TENSIONS}\n\n    adj = {}\n    for c1 in selected_concepts:\n        ca = concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n\n        # Find within-cluster candidates (prioritize tension pairs)\n        within_candidates = []\n        for c2 in selected_concepts:\n            if c1 == c2:\n                continue\n            cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")\n            if cb != ca:\n                continue\n            # Score by whether they're a tension pair\n            score = 1.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_PAIRS or (c2, c1) in TENSION_PAIRS else 0.5\n            within_candidates.append((c2, score))\n\n        # Sort by score desc, take top K\n        within_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, _ in within_candidates[:MAX_WITHIN_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n        # Cross-cluster edges\n        cross_candidates = []\n        for c2 in selected_concepts:\n            if c1 == c2:\n                continue\n            cb = concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\")\n            if cb == ca:\n                continue\n            w = CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((ca, cb), CROSS_WEIGHTS.get((cb, ca), 0.0))\n            if w > 0:\n                cross_candidates.append((c2, w))\n        cross_candidates.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n        for c2, w in cross_candidates[:MAX_CROSS_K]:\n            adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph = ConceptGraph(seed=42)\n    for c in selected_concepts:\n        graph.add_node(ConceptNode(id=c, activation=0.5))\n\n    for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n        graph.add_edge(a, b, w)\n        graph.add_edge(b, a, w)\n\n    # Goal concepts\n    goal_concepts = set()\n    for cluster_name in config[\"goal_clusters\"]:\n        if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n            for c in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                if c in selected_concepts:\n                    goal_concepts.add(c)\n\n    return graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, selected_concepts\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# DRIFT RUNNER\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef run_drift(\n    graph: ConceptGraph,\n    concept_to_cluster: dict,\n    goal_concepts: set,\n    steering: float = 0.3,\n    steps: int = 30,\n    diffusion_rate: float = 0.1,\n    decay_rate: float = 0.02,\n) -> tuple:\n    \"\"\"\n    Run drift cycle on the thematic graph.\n    Returns (final_graph, top_concepts, activation_history)\n\n    Note: steering uses cluster-based approach since thematic graph has no embeddings.\n    Goal-cluster nodes get periodic re-activation to counteract diffusion entropy.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Identify goal clusters\n    goal_clusters = set()\n    for concept, cluster in concept_to_cluster.items():\n        if concept in goal_concepts:\n            goal_clusters.add(cluster)\n\n    # Initialize: goal-cluster HIGH, others LOW\n    for node in graph.nodes.values():\n        if node.id in goal_concepts:\n            node.activation = 0.95\n        else:\n            cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n            if cluster in goal_clusters:\n                node.activation = 0.5\n            else:\n                node.activation = 0.05\n\n    config = DriftChamberConfig(\n        steering_strength=steering,\n        diffusion_rate=diffusion_rate,\n        decay_rate=decay_rate,\n        seed=42,\n        max_steps=steps,\n    )\n\n    history = []\n    for step in range(steps):\n        # Re-activate goal clusters every few steps to counteract diffusion entropy\n        # This IS the steering signal for the thematic graph (no embeddings needed)\n        if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0:\n            for node in graph.nodes.values():\n                cluster = concept_to_cluster.get(node.id, \"\")\n                if cluster in goal_clusters:\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.6)\n                elif node.id in goal_concepts:\n                    node.activation = max(node.activation, 0.8)\n\n        _, graph = drift_cycle(graph, None, config)\n        graph = decay(graph, rate=decay_rate)\n        history.append({\n            \"step\": step,\n            \"mean_activation\": sum(n.activation for n in graph.nodes.values()) / len(graph.nodes),\n            \"strong_nodes\": len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3)),\n        })\n\n    return graph, history\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# TEXT GENERATION — uses CreativeMapper from llm_mapper.py\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef generate_text(\n    top_concepts: list,\n    theme: str,\n    mode: str = \"creative\",\n    ollama_url: str = None,\n    model: str = \"qwen2.5:7b\",\n    seed_moment: str = None,\n    user_constraints: list = None,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Map top concepts to creative text using CreativeMapper.\n    Falls back to a poetic concept description if no LLM available.\n    \n    Args:\n        top_concepts: Ordered list of concept names (first = highest activation)\n        theme: The driving theme\n        mode: creative | divergent | exploratory\n        ollama_url: Ollama API URL (if None, uses OpenAI/Anthropic env vars)\n        model: Model name for Ollama\n        seed_moment: A specific moment/detail/seed text to anchor the piece\n        user_constraints: List of elements the user wants in the piece\n    \"\"\"\n    # Import CreativeMapper lazily\n    try:\n        from spark.core.llm_mapper import CreativeMapper, find_tensions_in_concepts, sample_drift_path\n    except ImportError:\n        return \"[ERROR: Could not import CreativeMapper. Run from spark/ directory or check PYTHONPATH.]\"\n\n    # Build activation dict from ordered concept list\n    # Earlier in list = higher activation\n    concept_activations = {}\n    for i, concept in enumerate(top_concepts):\n        # Decay activation based on position\n        activation = max(0.05, 0.95 - (i * 0.05))\n        concept_activations[concept] = activation\n\n    # Determine provider\n    if ollama_url:\n        provider = \"ollama\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"openai\"\n    elif os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n        provider = \"anthropic\"\n    else:\n        provider = \"ollama\"  # Default to Ollama if available locally\n\n    mapper = CreativeMapper(provider=provider, model=model)\n\n    # Patch Ollama URL at module level (CreativeMapper imports requests locally in _generate)\n    import requests as _req\n    original_post_fn = _req.post\n    if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n        _req.post = lambda url, json, timeout, **_kwargs: original_post_fn(\n            f\"{ollama_url}/api/generate\", json=json, timeout=timeout\n        )\n\n    try:\n        results = mapper.map_concepts_to_text(\n            concept_activations=concept_activations,\n            theme=theme,\n            mode=mode,\n            n_variations=1,\n            seed_moment=seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=user_constraints,\n        )\n        return results[0][\"text\"] if results else \"[No output]\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"[Generation error: {e}]\"\n    finally:\n        if ollama_url and provider == \"ollama\":\n            _req.post = original_post_fn\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# INTERACTIVE MODE\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef print_banner():\n    print()\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"  SPARK — Interactive Creative Writing Demo\")\n    print(\"  Drift Chamber + Thematic Graph + LLM\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print()\n\n\ndef print_domains():\n    print(\"Available domains:\")\n    for domain in [\"all\", \"romance\", \"scifi\", \"thriller\", \"literary\", \"horror\", \"poetry\"]:\n        desc = {\n            \"all\": \"All creative concepts\",\n            \"romance\": \"Love, longing, connection, loss\",\n            \"scifi\": \"Technology, cosmos, humanity, creation\",\n            \"thriller\": \"Tension, power, pursuit, secrets\",\n            \"literary\": \"Craft, meaning, form, expression\",\n            \"horror\": \"Death, dread, flesh, threshold\",\n            \"poetry\": \"Sensory, image, rhythm, metaphor\",\n        }[domain]\n        print(f\"  {domain:12s} — {desc}\")\n    print()\n\n\ndef print_modes():\n    print(\"Modes:\")\n    for mode in [\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"]:\n        desc = {\n            \"creative\": \"Balanced: coherent + exploratory\",\n            \"divergent\": \"Maximum surprise, subverts expectations\",\n            \"exploratory\": \"Contemplative, carefully observed\",\n        }[mode]\n        print(f\"  {mode:12s} — {desc}\")\n    print()\n\n\ndef interactive():\n    print_banner()\n    print_domains()\n    print_modes()\n\n    # Get user choices\n    domain = input(\"Domain [all]: \").strip().lower() or \"all\"\n    theme = input(\"Theme [love in the age of AI]: \").strip() or \"love in the age of AI\"\n    seed_moment = input(\"Seed moment / character detail (Enter to skip): \").strip() or None\n    if seed_moment:\n        print(f\"  ✓ Seed: {seed_moment[:60]}{'...' if len(seed_moment) > 60 else ''}\")\n    constraints_raw = input(\"Required elements (comma-separated, Enter to skip): \").strip() or None\n    user_constraints = [c.strip() for c in constraints_raw.split(\",\")] if constraints_raw else None\n    steering = float(input(\"Steering strength [0.3]: \").strip() or \"0.3\")\n    mode = input(\"Mode [creative]: \").strip().lower() or \"creative\"\n    n_outputs = int(input(\"Number of outputs [2]: \").strip() or \"2\")\n    ollama_url = input(\"Ollama URL (Enter to skip) [none]: \").strip() or None\n    if ollama_url and not ollama_url.startswith(\"http\"):\n        ollama_url = f\"http://{ollama_url}\"\n\n    print()\n    print(f\"Building {domain} concept graph...\")\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, concepts = build_thematic_graph(domain)\n    print(f\"  {len(graph.nodes)} concepts, {sum(len(n.neighbors) for n in graph.nodes.values())//2} edges\")\n\n    print(f\"Running drift (steering={steering}, steps=30)...\")\n    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, steering=steering)\n    print(f\"  Final: {len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))} strong concepts\")\n\n    # Get top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:20]]\n    top_clusters = [concept_to_cluster.get(c, \"unknown\") for c in top_concepts]\n\n    print()\n    print(\"TOP 20 ACTIVATED CONCEPTS:\")\n    for i, (c, cluster) in enumerate(zip(top_concepts[:10], top_clusters[:10])):\n        act = sorted_nodes[i].activation\n        bar = \"█\" * int(act * 20)\n        print(f\"  {i+1:2d}. {c:20s} [{cluster:12s}] {bar} {act:.2f}\")\n    if len(top_concepts) > 10:\n        print(f\"  ... and {len(top_concepts)-10} more\")\n    print()\n\n    # Generate text\n    for i in range(n_outputs):\n        print(f\"\\n--- OUTPUT {i+1}/{n_outputs} ---\\n\")\n        text = generate_text(\n            top_concepts, theme, mode, ollama_url,\n            seed_moment=seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=user_constraints,\n        )\n        print(text)\n        print()\n\n    seed_note = f\" --seed-moment '{seed_moment}'\" if seed_moment else \"\"\n    print(f\"\\nRegenerate: python demo.py --domain {domain} --steering {steering} --mode {mode}{seed_note} --ollama-url {ollama_url or ''}\")\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# MAIN\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"SPARK Interactive Creative Writing Demo\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--domain\", default=\"all\", choices=[\"all\", \"romance\", \"scifi\", \"thriller\", \"literary\", \"horror\", \"poetry\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--theme\", default=\"love in the age of AI\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--seed-moment\", default=None, help=\"A specific moment, character detail, or seed text to anchor the piece\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--constraints\", default=None, help=\"Comma-separated required elements\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--steering\", type=float, default=0.3)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--mode\", default=\"creative\", choices=[\"creative\", \"divergent\", \"exploratory\"])\n    parser.add_argument(\"--n\", type=int, default=2, help=\"Number of outputs\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--ollama-url\", default=None, help=\"Ollama API URL\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--model\", default=\"qwen2.5:7b\", help=\"Model name for Ollama\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--interactive\", action=\"store_true\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--list-domains\", action=\"store_true\")\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.list_domains:\n        print_banner()\n        print_domains()\n        print_modes()\n        return\n\n    user_constraints = [c.strip() for c in args.constraints.split(\",\")] if args.constraints else None\n\n    # Build graph\n    graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, concepts = build_thematic_graph(args.domain)\n    print(f\"[SPARK] {args.domain} graph: {len(graph.nodes)} concepts, {sum(len(n.neighbors) for n in graph.nodes.values())//2} edges\")\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Steering: {args.steering}, Mode: {args.mode}\")\n    if args.seed_moment:\n        print(f\"[SPARK] Seed: {args.seed_moment[:80]}{'...' if len(args.seed_moment) > 80 else ''}\")\n\n    # Run drift\n    graph, history = run_drift(graph, concept_to_cluster, goal_concepts, steering=args.steering)\n    strong = len(graph.get_strong_nodes(0.3))\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Drift complete: {strong} strong concepts | entropy: {activation_entropy(graph):.3f}\")\n\n    # Get top concepts\n    sorted_nodes = sorted(graph.nodes.values(), key=lambda n: n.activation, reverse=True)\n    top_concepts = [n.id for n in sorted_nodes[:20]]\n\n    print(f\"[SPARK] Top 10: {', '.join(top_concepts[:10])}\")\n\n    # Generate\n    for i in range(args.n):\n        print(f\"\\n{'='*60}\\nOUTPUT {i+1}/{args.n}\\n{'='*60}\")\n        text = generate_text(\n            top_concepts, args.theme, args.mode, args.ollama_url,\n            model=args.model,\n            seed_moment=args.seed_moment,\n            user_constraints=user_constraints,\n        )\n        print(text)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) == 1 or \"--interactive\" in sys.argv:\n        interactive()\n    else:\n        main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275268117}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee27777c","parentId":"65f3bf09","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:39.881Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture of the SPARK project. The modal setup is started but incomplete. What we need:\n\n1. **Finish modal setup** — The current `modal_ollama.py` just runs Ollama, but we need the full SPARK pipeline running on Modal with GPU. I need to create a Modal app that:\n   - Has Ollama running with GPU\n   - Runs the SPARK FastAPI server\n   - Exposes the API endpoints\n   - Has the drift chamber logic\n\n2. **Build a web UI** — A simple but polished HTML/CSS/JS UI that:\n   - Connects to the SPARK API\n   - Shows domain/mode/theme/steering controls\n   - Displays generated text with concept activations\n   - Has a nice visual design\n\nI should build this as a separate deployable web UI with its own infrastructure. My approach: create a complete Modal app that combines the Ollama GPU runtime with the SPARK FastAPI server, then build a React-based web UI to interact with it.","thinkingSignature":"9009d8a08fee81260702435d4e0451663c2073a1ea704f6dd9594e9b64ec9b0f"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — the modal_ollama.py has Ollama but not the full SPARK API wired up. And there's no web UI. Let me build both.\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Create a complete Modal app that runs the full SPARK FastAPI on A100 with embedded Ollama\n2. Build a React-based SPARK UI (served from Modal static hosting)\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8iu570g0o705_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark && ls deploy/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8iu570g0o705_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/deploy/modal_ollama.py","limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":16025,"output":379,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29997,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cac