{"type":"message","id":"a8cfb3da","parentId":"1f12173c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:14:41.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8iu570g0o705_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nSPARK Ollama GPU endpoint on Modal\nDeploy: modal deploy spark.deploy.modal_ollama\nEndpoint: https://spark-ollama-qwen-{user}.modal.run\n\"\"\"\n\nimport modal\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark-ollama\")\n\nollama_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\"requests\", \"httpx\", \"fastapi[standard]\")\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n    )\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\"})\n)\n\n\n\n[66 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774275281499}}
{"type":"message","id":"49fe459b","parentId":"a8cfb3da","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:17:09.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. I need to:\n\n1. Create a new Modal app that:\n   - Has Ollama with GPU\n   - Runs the SPARK API (FastAPI) on top of it\n   - Also serves a web UI\n\n2. Create the web UI - a React app in `spark/ui/`\n\nLet me create the full deployment setup. The key challenges:\n- Modal needs to run Ollama (GPU) + the FastAPI SPARK server\n- The web UI needs to be served statically from Modal\n- Ollama needs to auto-pull the model on first request\n\nFor the web UI, I'll build a polished React app with:\n\n\n- Domain/mode/theme/steering controls\n- Generated text display\n- Concept visualization\n- Clean, literary aesthetic\n\nLet me start with the Modal app, then build the UI.","thinkingSignature":"874297916ccf4511def60f4400533c6ce5eae22c590dfa2c3e02292a38ddf3ec"},{"type":"text","text":"Building the full stack now — Modal SPARK API + React UI:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c2h2rou3vxaj_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/deploy/spark_app.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSPARK — Full Modal Deployment\nRun: modal deploy spark.deploy.spark_app\n\nServes:\n  /v1/spark/generate  — creative text generation\n  /                   — SPARK web UI (static)\n  /health             — health check\n\"\"\"\n\nimport modal\nimport subprocess\nimport os\nimport signal\nimport sys\nimport json\nimport threading\nimport time\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# APP\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\napp = modal.App(\"spark\")\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# IMAGE — Ollama + SPARK dependencies\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nspark_image = (\n    modal.Image.debian_slim(python_version=\"3.11\")\n    .pip_install(\n        \"fastapi[standard]==0.115.0\",\n        \"uvicorn[standard]==0.30.0\",\n        \"requests==2.32.3\",\n        \"httpx==0.27.0\",\n        \"pydantic==2.9.0\",\n        \"numpy==1.26.4\",\n        \"networkx==3.4.2\",\n    )\n    .run_commands(\n        \"apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl zstd unzip && curl -fsSL https://ollama.com/install.sh | sh\",\n        _quiet=False,\n    )\n    .env({\"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\", \"OLLAMA_HOST\": \"0.0.0.0\"})\n)\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# VOLUME — persistent Ollama models\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nvolume = modal.Volume.from_name(\"spark-ollama-models\", create=True)\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DRIFT CHAMBER + THEMATIC GRAPH (embedded, no external deps)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nDRIFT_CHAMBER_CODE = '''\n\"\"\"Minimal drift chamber for Modal deployment.\"\"\"\n\nimport random\nimport networkx as nx\n\nWITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.3\nCROSS_CLUSTER_WEIGHT = 0.15\n\nCONCEPT_CLUSTERS = {\n    \"emotions\": [\"longing\", \"grief\", \"joy\", \"hope\", \"despair\", \"love\", \"hate\", \"fear\", \"shame\", \"awe\", \"nostalgia\", \"regret\", \"elation\", \"dread\", \"tenderness\"],\n    \"relationships\": [\"betrayal\", \"trust\", \"loyalty\", \"secrets\", \"confession\", \"reunion\", \"loss\", \"devotion\", \"estrangement\", \"reconciliation\", \"commitment\", \"betrayer\", \"beloved\"],\n    \"sensory\": [\"rain\", \"fire\", \"blood\", \"snow\", \"shadow\", \"light\", \"flesh\", \"iron\", \"salt\", \"glass\", \"mirror\", \"door\", \"threshold\", \"darkness\", \"heat\", \"cold\", \"smoke\", \"water\"],\n    \"cosmos\": [\"universe\", \"star\", \"void\", \"black_hole\", \"gravity\", \"silence\", \"infinity\", \"light_year\", \"extinction\", \"origins\", \"entropy\", \"cosmic\", \"orbit\", \"collapse\", \"singularity\"],\n    \"mortality\": [\"death\", \"dying\", \"ghost\", \"corpse\", \"grave\", \"afterlife\", \"memory\", \"forgetting\", \"bone\", \"decay\", \"resurrection\", \"sacrifice\", \"survival\", \"last_breath\", \"funeral\"],\n    \"narrative\": [\"pursuit\", \"escape\", \"revelation\", \"betrayal\", \"climax\", \"resolution\", \"setup\", \"misdirect\", \"backstory\", \"frame\", \"twist\", \"denouement\"],\n    \"creative\": [\"art\", \"story\", \"image\", \"word\", \"form\", \"fragment\", \"revision\", \"constraint\", \"voice\", \"style\", \"truth\", \"lie\", \"catharsis\", \"expression\", \"imitation\", \"originality\"],\n    \"literary\": [\"sentence\", \"paragraph\", \"page\", \"chapter\", \"narrator\", \"perspective\", \"tension\", \"rhythm\", \"pace\", \"ending\", \"opening\", \"image\", \"symbol\", \"motif\", \"leitmotif\"],\n    \"archetypes\": [\"mother\", \"father\", \"child\", \"stranger\", \"mentor\", \"shadow_self\", \"trickster\", \"hero\", \"villain\", \"victim\", \"rebel\", \"outcast\", \"prophet\", \"fool\"],\n    \"nature\": [\"forest\", \"ocean\", \"desert\", \"mountain\", \"river\", \"storm\", \"sunset\", \"sunrise\", \"season\", \"winter\", \"summer\", \"autumn\", \"spring\", \"flood\", \"drought\", \"earth\", \"sky\"],\n}\n\nDOMAIN_CONFIGS = {\n    \"all\":         {\"clusters\": list(CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.keys()),                  \"goal_clusters\": [\"creative\", \"emotions\"]},\n    \"romance\":     {\"clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\", \"sensory\"],         \"goal_clusters\": [\"emotions\", \"relationships\"]},\n    \"scifi\":       {\"clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\", \"mortality\"],             \"goal_clusters\": [\"cosmos\", \"creative\"]},\n    \"thriller\":    {\"clusters\": [\"narrative\", \"cosmos\", \"relationships\"],         \"goal_clusters\": [\"narrative\", \"cosmos\"]},\n    \"literary\":    {\"clusters\": [\"literary\", \"creative\", \"emotions\"],            \"goal_clusters\": [\"literary\", \"creative\"]},\n    \"horror\":      {\"clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\", \"emotions\"],            \"goal_clusters\": [\"mortality\", \"sensory\"]},\n    \"poetry\":      {\"clusters\": [\"sensory\", \"literary\", \"creative\", \"emotions\"],\"goal_clusters\": [\"sensory\", \"creative\"]},\n}\n\n\nclass DriftChamber:\n    def __init__(self, domain=\"all\", seed=42):\n        self.domain = domain\n        self.seed = seed\n        self.graph = None\n        self.concept_to_cluster = {}\n        self.goal_concepts = set()\n        self.all_concepts = []\n        self.history = []\n        self._build_graph()\n\n    def _build_graph(self):\n        config = DOMAIN_CONFIGS.get(self.domain, DOMAIN_CONFIGS[\"all\"])\n        selected = []\n        for cluster_name in config[\"clusters\"]:\n            if cluster_name in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n                for concept in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cluster_name]:\n                    if concept not in selected:\n                        selected.append(concept)\n\n        self.concept_to_cluster = {}\n        for cn, concepts in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS.items():\n            for c in concepts:\n                if c not in self.concept_to_cluster:\n                    self.concept_to_cluster[c] = cn\n\n        TENSION_PAIRS = {\n            (\"light\", \"darkness\"), (\"creation\", \"destruction\"), (\"love\", \"hate\"),\n            (\"order\", \"chaos\"), (\"birth\", \"death\"), (\"hope\", \"despair\"),\n            (\"truth\", \"lie\"), (\"memory\", \"forgetting\"), (\"ghost\", \"flesh\"),\n        }\n\n        adj = {}\n        for c1 in selected:\n            ca = self.concept_to_cluster.get(c1, \"\")\n            # Within-cluster (max 6 neighbors, prefer tensions)\n            within = []\n            for c2 in selected:\n                if c1 == c2:\n                    continue\n                if self.concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\") != ca:\n                    continue\n                score = 2.0 if (c1, c2) in TENSION_PAIRS or (c2, c1) in TENSION_PAIRS else 1.0\n                within.append((c2, score))\n            within.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n            for c2, _ in within[:6]:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = WITHIN_CLUSTER_WEIGHT\n\n            # Cross-cluster (max 4)\n            cross = []\n            for c2 in selected:\n                if c1 == c2:\n                    continue\n                if self.concept_to_cluster.get(c2, \"\") == ca:\n                    continue\n                cross.append((c2, CROSS_CLUSTER_WEIGHT))\n            cross.sort(key=lambda x: -x[1])\n            for c2, w in cross[:4]:\n                adj[(c1, c2)] = w\n\n        self.graph = nx.Graph()\n        for c in selected:\n            self.graph.add_node(c, activation=0.05)\n        for (a, b), w in adj.items():\n            self.graph.add_edge(a, b, weight=w)\n\n        self.all_concepts = selected\n        self.goal_concepts = set()\n        for cn in config[\"goal_clusters\"]:\n            if cn in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS:\n                for c in CONCEPT_CLUSTERS[cn]:\n                    if c in selected:\n                        self.goal_concepts.add(c)\n\n    def run(self, steering=0.3, steps=30, diffusion_rate=0.1, decay_rate=0.02):\n        rng = random.Random(self.seed)\n        goal_clusters = {self.concept_to_cluster.get(c, \"\") for c in self.goal_concepts}\n\n        # Init activations\n        for node in self.graph.nodes:\n            if node in self.goal_concepts:\n                self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = 0.95\n            elif self.concept_to_cluster.get(node, \"\") in goal_clusters:\n                self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = 0.5\n            else:\n                self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = 0.05\n\n        self.history = []\n        for step in range(steps):\n            if step > 0 and step % 4 == 0 and steering > 0:\n                for node in self.graph.nodes:\n                    cluster = self.concept_to_cluster.get(node, \"\")\n                    if cluster in goal_clusters:\n                        self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = max(self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"], 0.6)\n                    if node in self.goal_concepts:\n                        self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = max(self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"], 0.8)\n\n            # Diffusion\n            new_act = {}\n            for node in self.graph.nodes:\n                neighbors = list(self.graph.neighbors(node))\n                if not neighbors:\n                    new_act[node] = self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"]\n                    continue\n                total_w = sum(self.graph.edges[node, n].get(\"weight\", 0.3) for n in neighbors)\n                if total_w == 0:\n                    new_act[node] = self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"]\n                    continue\n                neighbor_act = sum(\n                    self.graph.nodes[n][\"activation\"] * self.graph.edges[node, n].get(\"weight\", 0.3)\n                    for n in neighbors\n                ) / total_w\n                new_act[node] = (1 - diffusion_rate) * self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] + diffusion_rate * neighbor_act\n\n            for node in self.graph.nodes:\n                self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = new_act[node]\n\n            # Steering toward goal concepts\n            if steering > 0:\n                for node in self.goal_concepts:\n                    self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] = min(\n                        1.0,\n                        self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] + steering * 0.15\n                    )\n\n            # Decay\n            for node in self.graph.nodes:\n                self.graph.nodes[node][\"activation\"] *= (1 - decay_rate)\n\n            self.history.append({\n                \"step\": step,\n                \"mean\": sum(n[\"activation\"] for n in self.graph.nodes.values()) / len(self.graph.nodes),\n                \"strong\": sum(1 for n in self.graph.nodes.values() if n[\"activation\"] > 0.3),\n            })\n\n        return self\n\n    def top_concepts(self, n=20, threshold=0.05):\n        nodes = sorted(self.graph.nodes, key=lambda n: self.graph.nodes[n][\"activation\"], reverse=True)\n        return [(c, self.graph.nodes[c][\"activation\"]) for c in nodes[:n] if self.graph.nodes[c][\"activation\"] > threshold]\n\n    def entropy(self):\n        acts = [self.graph.nodes[n][\"activation\"] for n in self.graph.nodes]\n        total = sum(acts)\n        if total == 0:\n            return 0.0\n        import math\n        return -sum((a / total) * math.log2(a / total) for a in acts if a > 0)\n'''\n\nexec(DRIFT_CHAMBER_CODE.strip())\n\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# LLM MAPPER (inline — no external spark/ imports needed on Modal)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nLLM_MAPPER_CODE = '''\nimport os, json, random, math\n\nSPARK_VOICE = \"\"\"You are SPARK. Not a writing workshop. Not a Hallmark card.\nReal prose. The kind where something is at stake.\nPrecision of image. Emotion earned through concrete detail, not declared.\nSentences that do real work. Endings that open rather than close.\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_CREATIVE = \"\"\"SPARK creative voice:\n- Ground every abstraction in a concrete sensory moment\n- Let the emotional logic be complex, not simple\n- A character can want two contradictory things\n- What\\'s unsaid matters more than what\\'s said\n- End on an image that contains the whole feeling\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_DIVERGENT = \"\"\"SPARK divergent voice:\n- Break expected form. Break expected rhythm.\n- Let the sentence become the thought\n- Association over narration\n- Surprising juxtapositions earn their place\"\"\"\n\nSPARK_EXPLORATORY = \"\"\"SPARK exploratory voice:\n- Patient attention to the overlooked\n- Small things seen clearly\n- Restraint is a form of precision\n- Let silence do work\"\"\"\n\nCREATIVE_TENSIONS = [\n    (\"light\", \"darkness\", 0.95), (\"creation\", \"destruction\", 0.95),\n    (\"love\", \"hate\", 0.90), (\"birth\", \"death\", 0.90),\n    (\"hope\", \"despair\", 0.85), (\"memory\", \"forgetting\", 0.80),\n    (\"loyalty\", \"betrayal\", 0.85), (\"voice\", \"silence\", 0.75),\n]\n\n\ndef find_tensions(concepts):\n    found = []\n    cs = set(concepts)\n    for a, b, w in CREATIVE_TENSIONS:\n        if a in cs and b in cs:\n            found.append((a, b))\n    return found\n\n\ndef sample_path(activations, n=5):\n    sorted_c = sorted(activations.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\n    top = [c for c, a in sorted_c[:10] if a > 0.5]\n    mid = [c for c, a in sorted_c[10:25] if a > 0.3]\n    path = []\n    k = n // 2\n    if top:\n        path.extend(random.sample(top, min(len(top), k)))\n    if mid:\n        path.extend(random.sample(mid, min(len(mid), n - len(path))))\n    random.shuffle(path)\n    return path[:n]\n\n\ndef build_prompt(theme, concepts, entropy_val, mode, seed, constraints):\n    primary = \", \".join([c for c, _ in concepts[:8]])\n    drift = \" → \".join(sample_path(dict(concepts)))\n    tensions = find_tensions([c for c, _ in concepts])\n    tension_str = \"Track: \" + \"; \".join(f\"{a} vs {b}\" for a, b in tensions[:3]) + \".\" if tensions else \"\"\n    constraints_str = \"\\\\nUser wants: \" + \", \".join(constraints) + \".\" if constraints else \"\"\n    seed_str = f'\\\\nSeed moment to build from: \"{seed}\"' if seed else \"\"\n\n    if mode == \"divergent\":\n        return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_DIVERGENT}\n\nA brief, strange piece (100-200 words) about: {theme}\n\nConcepts: {primary}\nDrift path: {drift}\n{tension_str}{constraints_str}{seed_str}\n\nBreak form. Surprising associations earn their place. End on an image that contains a world.\"\"\"\n\n    elif mode == \"exploratory\":\n        return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_EXPLORATORY}\n\nA contemplative piece (200-300 words) about: {theme}\n\n{primary}\nDrift: {drift}\n{tension_str}{constraints_str}{seed_str}\n\nSmall things, seen clearly. Restraint is precision. Let silence do the work.\"\"\"\n\n    else:\n        return f\"\"\"{SPARK_VOICE}\n\n{SPARK_CREATIVE}\n\nA short literary fiction piece (200-300 words) about: {theme}\n\nPrimary concepts: {primary}\nThe drift path: {drift}\n{tension_str}{constraints_str}{seed_str}\n\nDo NOT:\n- Start with \"The [time] [character] felt [emotion]\"\n- End with a moral or lesson\n- Use \"in that moment\" or \"journey\"\n- Simple resolution\n\nDo:\n- Ground abstractions in sensory detail\n- Let the ending open\n- Earn emotion through what you show\"\"\"\n\n\ndef generate_via_ollama(prompt, model, ollama_base_url, temperature, max_tokens):\n    import requests\n    resp = requests.post(\n        f\"{ollama_base_url}/api/generate\",\n        json={\"model\": model, \"prompt\": prompt, \"stream\": False,\n              \"options\": {\"temperature\": temperature, \"num_predict\": max_tokens}},\n        timeout=120,\n    )\n    resp.raise_for_status()\n    return resp.json().get(\"response\", \"\").strip()\n\n\ndef generate_text(concepts, theme, mode, seed, constraints, ollama_url, model):\n    prompt = build_prompt(theme, concepts, 0, mode, seed, constraints or [])\n    temp = {\"creative\": 0.8, \"divergent\": 1.1, \"exploratory\": 0.7}[mode]\n    max_tok = {\"creative\": 600, \"divergent\": 400, \"exploratory\": 600}[mode]\n    return generate_via_ollama(prompt, model or \"qwen2.5:7b\", ollama_url, temp, max_tok)\n'''\n\nexec(LLM_MAPPER_CODE.strip())\n\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WEB UI — embedded HTML\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nWEB_UI = '''\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"/>\n<title>SPARK — Creative Intelligence</title>\n<style>\n  @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Crimson+Pro:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,600;1,300;1,400&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap');\n\n  :root {\n    --bg: #0d0d0f;\n    --surface: #141418;\n    --border: #222228;\n    --text: #e8e4df;\n    --muted: #7a7772;\n    --accent: #c8a96e;\n    --accent2: #6e8fc8;\n    --dim: #3a3835;\n  }\n\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n  body {\n    background: var(--bg);\n    color: var(--text);\n    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;\n    font-size: 18px;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n    min-height: 100vh;\n  }\n\n  /* ── HEADER ── */\n  header {\n    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: baseline;\n    gap: 1.5rem;\n  }\n  header h1 {\n    font-size: 1.6rem;\n    font-weight: 300;\n    letter-spacing: 0.3em;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    color: var(--accent);\n  }\n  header p {\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-style: italic;\n  }\n\n  /* ── MAIN LAYOUT ── */\n  main {\n    display: grid;\n    grid-template-columns: 320px 1fr;\n    min-height: calc(100vh - 80px);\n  }\n\n  /* ── SIDEBAR ── */\n  aside {\n    border-right: 1px solid var(--border);\n    padding: 1.5rem;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 1.2rem;\n  }\n\n  .control-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }\n  .control-group label {\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.12em;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n  }\n\n  select, input[type=\"text\"], textarea {\n    background: var(--surface);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    color: var(--text);\n    font-family: inherit;\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    outline: none;\n    transition: border-color 0.2s;\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n  select:focus, input[type=\"text\"]:focus, textarea:focus {\n    border-color: var(--accent);\n  }\n  textarea {\n    resize: vertical;\n    min-height: 60px;\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n\n  /* Steering slider */\n  .steering-wrap { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }\n  .steering-header { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }\n  .steering-value {\n    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n    color: var(--accent2);\n  }\n  input[type=\"range\"] {\n    width: 100%;\n    accent-color: var(--accent);\n    cursor: pointer;\n  }\n\n  /* Generate button */\n  #generate-btn {\n    background: var(--accent);\n    color: #0d0d0f;\n    border: none;\n    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;\n    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.15em;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    transition: opacity 0.2s, transform 0.1s;\n    margin-top: 0.5rem;\n  }\n  #generate-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }\n  #generate-btn:active { transform: scale(0.98); }\n  #generate-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.4; cursor: not-allowed; }\n\n  /* ── OUTPUT ── */\n  #output-pane {\n    padding: 2rem;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n  }\n\n  .output-card {\n    background: var(--surface);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;\n    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;\n    animation: fadein 0.4s ease;\n  }\n  @keyframes fadein { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }\n\n  .output-meta {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 1rem;\n    margin-bottom: 1rem;\n    flex-wrap: wrap;\n  }\n  .output-meta span {\n    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 0.7rem;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.1em;\n    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    background: var(--border);\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .output-meta span.regime { background: rgba(200,169,110,0.15); color: var(--accent); }\n\n  .output-text {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    line-height: 1.75;\n    color: var(--text);\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n  }\n\n  /* Concept bar chart */\n  .concept-viz {\n    margin-top: 1.2rem;\n    padding-top: 1rem;\n    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);\n  }\n  .concept-viz-title {\n    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 0.65rem;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.1em;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;\n  }\n  .concept-row {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 0.6rem;\n    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;\n  }\n  .concept-name {\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    width: 110px;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    text-overflow: ellipsis;\n    white-space: nowrap;\n  }\n  .concept-bar-wrap {\n    flex: 1;\n    height: 4px;\n    background: var(--dim);\n    border-radius: 2px;\n    overflow: hidden;\n  }\n  .concept-bar { height: 100%; background: var(--accent); border-radius: 2px; }\n  .concept-val {\n    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;\n    font-size: 0.7rem;\n    color: var(--accent2);\n    width: 30px;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n\n  /* Loading spinner */\n  .loading {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    gap: 1rem;\n    height: 200px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-style: italic;\n  }\n  .spinner {\n    width: 32px; height: 32px;\n    border: 2px solid var(--border);\n    border-top-color: var(--accent);\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    animation: spin 0.8s linear infinite;\n  }\n  @keyframes spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }\n\n  /* Empty state */\n  .empty-state {\n    height: 100%;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-style: italic;\n    gap: 0.5rem;\n  }\n  .empty-state strong { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 300; color: var(--dim); }\n\n  /* Error */\n  .error-msg {\n    background: rgba(180,60,60,0.15);\n    border: 1px solid rgba(180,60,60,0.3);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;\n    color: #e07070;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<header>\n  <h1>SPARK</h1>\n  <p>Semantic Pattern Recognition via Associative Drift</p>\n</header>\n\n<main>\n  <aside>\n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Domain</label>\n      <select id=\"domain\">\n        <option value=\"all\">All — Full creative range</option>\n        <option value=\"romance\">Romance — Love, longing, loss</option>\n        <option value=\"scifi\">Sci-Fi — Tech, cosmos, creation</option>\n        <option value=\"thriller\">Thriller — Tension, pursuit, secrets</option>\n        <option value=\"literary\">Literary — Craft, meaning, form</option>\n        <option value=\"horror\">Horror — Death, dread, flesh</option>\n        <option value=\"poetry\">Poetry — Image, rhythm, metaphor</option>\n      </select>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Mode</label>\n      <select id=\"mode\">\n        <option value=\"creative\">Creative — Balanced & alive</option>\n        <option value=\"divergent\">Divergent — Maximum surprise</option>\n        <option value=\"exploratory\">Exploratory — Contemplative</option>\n      </select>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Theme</label>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"theme\" placeholder=\"love in the age of AI\" value=\"love in the age of AI\"/>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Seed Moment (optional)</label>\n      <textarea id=\"seed\" placeholder=\"A character detail, moment, or image to anchor the piece...\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"control-group\">\n      <label>Required Elements (optional)</label>\n      <input type=\"text\" id=\"constraints\" placeholder=\"rain, betrayal, a door\"/>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"steering-wrap\">\n      <div class=\"steering-header\">\n        <label>Drift Steering</label>\n        <span class=\"steering-value\" id=\"steer-val\">0.30</span>\n      </div>\n      <input type=\"range\" id=\"steering\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.05\" value=\"0.3\"/>\n      <div style=\"display:flex;justify-content:space-between;font-size:0.65rem;color:var(--dim);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;\">\n        <span>Pure Drift</span>\n        <span>Guided</span>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"control-group\" style=\"flex-direction:row;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:0.5rem;\">\n      <div style=\"flex:1;\">\n        <label>Variations</label>\n        <select id=\"n\">\n          <option value=\"1\">1</option>\n          <option value=\"2\" selected>2</option>\n          <option value=\"3\">3</option>\n        </select>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"flex:1;\">\n        <label>Steps</label>\n        <select id=\"steps\">\n          <option value=\"20\">20</option>\n          <option value=\"30\" selected>30</option>\n          <option value=\"50\">50</option>\n        </select>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <button id=\"generate-btn\" onclick=\"generate()\">▲ Spark</button>\n    <p style=\"font-size:0.7rem;color:var(--dim);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;text-align:center;\">\n      Powered by Qwen2.5 on Modal A100\n    </p>\n  </aside>\n\n  <div id=\"output-pane\">\n    <div class=\"empty-state\">\n      <strong>Your turn.</strong>\n      Configure a prompt and hit Spark.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</main>\n\n<script>\n  const API = window.location.origin;\n\n  document.getElementById('steering').addEventListener('input', function() {\n    document.getElementById('steer-val').textContent = parseFloat(this.value).toFixed(2);\n  });\n\n  async function generate() {\n    const btn = document.getElementById('generate-btn');\n    const pane = document.getElementById('output-pane');\n\n    const req = {\n      theme: document.getElementById('theme').value || \"love in the age of AI\",\n      domain: document.getElementById('domain').value,\n      mode: document.getElementById('mode').value,\n      steering: parseFloat(document.getElementById('steering').value),\n      n: parseInt(document.getElementById('n').value),\n      steps: parseInt(document.getElementById('steps').value),\n      seed_moment: document.getElementById('seed').value || null,\n      constraints: document.getElementById('constraints').value\n        ? document.getElementById('constraints').value.split(\",\").map(s=>s.trim()).filter(Boolean)\n        : null,\n    };\n\n    btn.disabled = true;\n    btn.textContent = \"Igniting...\";\n    pane.innerHTML = '<div class=\"loading\"><div class=\"spinner\"></div><span>Running drift chamber...</span></div>';\n\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch(API + \"/v1/spark/generate\", {\n        method: \"POST\",\n        headers: {\"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"},\n        body: JSON.stringify(req),\n      });\n\n      if (!res.ok) {\n        const err = await res.json().catch(()=>({}));\n        throw new Error(err.detail || `HTTP ${res.status}`);\n      }\n\n      const data = await res.json();\n      renderResults(data);\n    } catch(e) {\n      pane.innerHTML = `<div class=\"error-msg\">⚠ ${e.message}</div>`;\n    } finally {\n      btn.disabled = false;\n      btn.textContent = \"▲ Spark\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  function renderResults(data) {\n    const pane = document.getElementById('output-pane');\n    if (!data.variations || data.variations.length === 0) {\n      pane.innerHTML = '<div class=\"empty-state\"><strong>No output.</strong> Try different settings.</div>';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    pane.innerHTML = data.variations.map(v => `\n      <div class=\"output-card\">\n        <div class=\"output-meta\">\n          <span>${data.meta.mode}</span>\n          <span>steering ${data.meta.steering}</span>\n          <span>${data.meta.n_concepts} concepts</span>\n          <span>${data.meta.entropy} bits</span>\n          <span class=\"regime\">${data.meta.regime}</span>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"output-text\">${escapeHtml(v.text)}</div>\n        <div class=\"concept-viz\">\n          <div class=\"concept-viz-title\">Activated Concepts</div>\n          ${v.concepts.slice(0, 12).map((c, i) => `\n            <div class=\"concept-row\">\n              <span class=\"concept-name\">${escapeHtml(c)}</span>\n              <div class=\"concept-bar-wrap\">\n                <div class=\"concept-bar\" style=\"width:${(v.concepts.length - i) / v.concepts.length * 100}%\"></div>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          `).join('')}\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    `).join('');\n  }\n\n  function escapeHtml(str) {\n    return String(str)\n      .replace(/&/g, \"&amp;\")\n      .replace(/</g, \"&lt;\")\n      .replace(/>/g, \"&gt;\")\n      .replace(/\"/g, \"&quot;\");\n  }\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\n'''\n\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# FASTAPI APP (runs inside Modal class)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n@app.cls(\n    image=spark_image,\n    gpu=\"A100\",\n    memory=32768,\n    volumes={\"/root/.ollama\": volume},\n    scaledown_window=600,\n    timeout=3600,\n    container_idle_timeout=300,\n)\nclass SparkAPI:\n\n    @modal.enter()\n    def start(self):\n        import subprocess, os, signal, sys, time\n\n        self._ollama_pid = None\n\n        # Start ollama serve in background\n        print(\"[spark] Starting ollama serve...\", file=sys.stderr)\n        self._proc = subprocess.Popen(\n            [\"ollama\", \"serve\"],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.STDOUT,\n            preexec_fn=os.setsid,\n            env={**os.environ, \"OLLAMA_MODELS\": \"/root/.ollama\"},\n        )\n        self._ollama_pid = self._proc.pid\n        print(f\"[spark] ollama serve started, pid={self._proc.pid}\", file=sys.stderr)\n\n        # Wait for ollama to be ready\n        import requests\n        for attempt in range(30):\n            try:\n                r = requests.get(\"http://localhost:11434\", timeout=2)\n                if r.status_code == 200:\n                    print(\"[spark] Ollama is ready\", file=sys.stderr)\n                    break\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n            time.sleep(2)\n        else:\n            print(\"[spark] WARNING: Ollama may not be fully ready\", file=sys.stderr)\n\n        # Pre"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":16739,"output":8192,"cacheRead":13593,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38524,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"length","timestamp":1774275281548}}
